WEBVTT

00:00.802 --> 00:03.044
Welcome to the James River Church Podcast.

00:03.285 --> 00:06.989
You're about to hear another inspirational message from Pastor John Lindwell.

00:07.009 --> 00:08.851
Lead pastor at James River Church.

00:09.171 --> 00:14.437
It's our prayer that this message is an encouragement and blessing to your life.

00:14.457 --> 00:19.783
I want to take a few moments and just briefly talk to you about hearing the voice of God.

00:19.803 --> 00:26.610
I think it's one of the most important things a Christian will learn to do.

00:27.842 --> 00:36.814
is to be able to process the difference between their own inner voice and the prompting of the Holy Spirit to their heart.

00:37.795 --> 00:38.797
Now, let me just say this.

00:38.817 --> 00:44.164
When we're talking about the voice of God, some of you are saying, so God audibly speaks to you.

00:44.925 --> 00:47.108
I believe God has done that to people.

00:47.168 --> 00:51.434
In fact, I have met people who have told me of their encounter.

00:51.494 --> 00:52.375
I believe it to be true.

00:52.735 --> 00:54.738
Some people have actually had Jesus appear to them.

00:56.034 --> 00:57.836
So I believe that to be true.

00:58.677 --> 01:09.127
I have never personally experienced that, and yet at the same time, I know there are moments regularly in my life where the Lord speaks to my heart.

01:10.689 --> 01:16.315
Where the Lord, He may speak to your heart by His still small voice speaking to you.

01:16.555 --> 01:18.217
This should not surprise any Christian.

01:18.277 --> 01:23.442
Let me just back up long enough to say, Christians through the ages have understood God speaks.

01:24.802 --> 01:31.113
The old ham in the garden and he walks with me and he talks with me and he tells me that I am his own.

01:31.413 --> 01:35.340
This should not be shocking to any Christian.

01:35.360 --> 01:40.629
What shocking is, there's a lot of Christian churches that no longer talk about this.

01:41.050 --> 01:42.032
That's what shocking.

01:43.354 --> 01:45.318
But God wants to speak to his people.

01:46.339 --> 01:47.922
It's very, very interesting that

01:48.066 --> 01:49.467
Over 3,800 times.

01:49.507 --> 01:52.350
Now think about this, over 3,800 times.

01:52.430 --> 01:58.837
And this is from Dr. Bill McCray, the president of Tyndale University College and seminary.

01:59.297 --> 02:10.909
He says this, on 3,800 occasions, there is a phrase in the Bible that says God said, thus saith the Lord, or the word of the Lord came to a person.

02:10.929 --> 02:16.434
3,800 times in the Bible.

02:17.826 --> 02:19.228
God is the God who speaks.

02:21.271 --> 02:22.593
God has a lot to say.

02:22.633 --> 02:27.561
The question is, are you and I listening?

02:27.581 --> 02:36.054
And are we growing in our ability to discern when it's the Lord, when it's us, and to discern the different ways God may speak to us?

02:37.476 --> 02:43.826
Sometimes it's as simple as one of the things when I'm praying, I like to have something I can ride on

02:43.906 --> 02:47.912
My phone's fine, I find the phone to be a distraction, honestly.

02:49.093 --> 02:59.689
So to have something you can write on, so when a thought comes into your mind that is, you just know, God gave you that thought.

03:01.551 --> 03:05.097
Or you might be going through your day and have the Lord speak to you.

03:06.459 --> 03:11.666
Sunday morning, I was sitting in the first service and as I was sitting there out of the blue,

03:11.810 --> 03:14.977
God puts a person on my mind with a word for them.

03:15.237 --> 03:15.758
He spoke.

03:17.241 --> 03:24.056
I'm excited that we're in a church where God is speaking, and so when people are coming up and they're giving a word of knowledge, how are they doing that?

03:24.396 --> 03:25.138
The Lord has

03:25.282 --> 03:27.425
placed in their heart what to say.

03:27.826 --> 03:34.334
And the proof that it's God is we're seeing all these people that are being healed today in our book study with the college.

03:34.475 --> 03:36.818
Several students got up and it was testimony.

03:36.838 --> 03:39.522
He's like, I saw a first time guests come to youth.

03:39.862 --> 03:46.271
He was on crutches and the instant he came in, one of our students said, I knew God was gonna heal him.

03:46.391 --> 03:47.953
I just knew it instantly was gonna be healed.

03:48.194 --> 03:51.538
And he was, he walked out with our crutches.

03:51.558 --> 03:54.322
So God is a God.

03:54.434 --> 03:55.876
who speaks to us.

03:57.377 --> 04:00.241
He wants to tell you things.

04:01.983 --> 04:06.548
I think Jeremiah says, seek me and I'll tell you on searchable things you do not know.

04:08.170 --> 04:14.497
God wants to tell you and I what we don't know that we need to know that would help us.

04:16.679 --> 04:22.386
Now, I'm going to say this as well, and God works differently with different people, but

04:22.754 --> 04:37.497
My experience has been that unless it's a situation often where I can think of a few instances where I prayed, I just said, I've got to get an answer from God, and I'm not leaving until I get an answer.

04:39.239 --> 04:41.303
And after four hours, the Lord spoke to me.

04:42.665 --> 04:46.130
I had the answer, and it was attended by His presence.

04:46.498 --> 04:48.901
So I do believe God can do that.

04:48.921 --> 05:02.775
I also believe that I can think of one time when Debbie and I were serving in a situation on a staff and I just really knew I needed to move on at the time.

05:02.815 --> 05:13.106
The problem is I'm 22 and I'm wanting to pastor and there's not a real market for 22 year old pastors, but I'm praying that God's gonna open the door for that to happen and

05:13.186 --> 05:17.731
And I have a lot of people telling me that's never going to happen, which that never seems to bother me.

05:17.851 --> 05:22.336
That when you tell me it's not going to happen, I just felt like, yeah, probably God's going to prove you wrong.

05:23.357 --> 05:24.999
So I just have that sense.

05:25.019 --> 05:25.960
This is how I roll.

05:26.481 --> 05:27.542
So anyway, I'm praying.

05:27.582 --> 05:29.224
And I can tell you where I was praying.

05:29.764 --> 05:31.947
It was where I had a regular prayer time.

05:32.267 --> 05:38.514
And the Lord spoke to my heart and said, I'm going to give you a church.

05:39.042 --> 05:41.966
This will be a sign to you because Debbie was carrying David.

05:42.407 --> 05:45.111
And in that time, I think it's still probably that way today.

05:45.592 --> 05:50.659
If the woman carrying the baby doesn't want to know the sex of the child, they're not going to tell the husband.

05:50.699 --> 05:54.425
And so I was like, I really want to know.

05:54.485 --> 05:57.449
And I'd hoped it was a boy, but it had been fine if it had been a girl.

05:57.509 --> 06:02.537
But I was just praying and about finding a church.

06:02.677 --> 06:04.399
That was a bigger concern to me at the moment.

06:05.261 --> 06:08.946
And the Lord said, the baby Debbie's carrying

06:09.090 --> 06:14.576
is a boy to be assigned to you that six months from the day he's born, you'll be pastoring.

06:15.718 --> 06:16.959
That's very specific.

06:18.641 --> 06:21.404
So David was born on September 29th.

06:21.805 --> 06:26.210
We took the church on March 28th, the following spring.

06:26.570 --> 06:28.252
And it was a church I had turned down.

06:28.293 --> 06:30.215
It was a church I was not interested in going to.

06:30.235 --> 06:31.276
They still voted me in.

06:31.596 --> 06:36.402
So it wasn't like I was trying to make it happen.

06:38.018 --> 06:38.919
It's the voice of the Lord.

06:38.939 --> 06:40.401
He can get very specific with you.

06:41.442 --> 06:55.839
Oftentimes though what happens is it's things I'm praying about or things, maybe just things I need to know and I can be going somewhere, driving somewhere, sitting in my office.

06:56.240 --> 07:01.847
I can be doing different things and all of a sudden the Lord speaks and I know that it's the Lord.

07:03.529 --> 07:07.954
I would suggest to you the best way to hear the voice of God is to be a peace.

07:09.346 --> 07:12.469
in your spirit relative to life in general.

07:14.131 --> 07:21.359
But it's hard to hear the voice of God when you're worked up or when you are dealing with anxiety.

07:23.121 --> 07:32.531
But to rest in the Lord, and in that moment, just to trust Him with the things of life, as pressing as they may be, oftentimes opens us up to the voice of the Lord.

07:34.173 --> 07:38.898
Tonight, what I wanna do is I wanna talk to you about how you're listening, and then next week,

07:39.682 --> 07:41.004
How to hear God's voice.

07:42.005 --> 07:43.688
Let's look at it for Samuel chapter three.

07:43.708 --> 07:46.312
One of my favorite stories in the book of Samuel.

07:46.612 --> 07:50.017
First Samuel, the boy Samuel ministered before the Lord under Eli.

07:50.418 --> 07:52.140
In those days, the word of the Lord was rare.

07:52.481 --> 07:53.502
There were not many visions.

07:54.283 --> 07:59.391
One night, Eli, whose eyes were becoming so weak that he could barely see, was lying down in his usual place.

08:00.112 --> 08:01.975
The lamp of God had not yet gone out.

08:02.796 --> 08:06.942
And Samuel was lying down in the temple of the Lord, where the ark of God was.

08:08.144 --> 08:09.586
Then the Lord called Samuel,

08:09.698 --> 08:11.320
Samuel answered, here am I.

08:11.340 --> 08:20.890
He ran the Eli, Eli's the high priest and said, he ran to Eli and said, here I am, you called me.

08:20.910 --> 08:23.353
But Eli said, I did not call, go back and lie down.

08:23.593 --> 08:24.715
So he went and lay down.

08:24.735 --> 08:31.082
Again, the Lord called Samuel and Samuel got up and went to Eli and said, here I am, you called me.

08:31.522 --> 08:34.185
My son Eli said, I did not call, go back and lie down.

08:34.225 --> 08:38.450
Now Samuel did not yet know the Lord.

08:39.074 --> 08:42.258
The word of the Lord had not yet been revealed to him.

08:42.638 --> 08:45.161
So this is the very first time you may have never heard.

08:45.442 --> 08:46.683
This should be very encouraging to you.

08:46.903 --> 08:48.525
You may have never heard the voice of the Lord.

08:50.508 --> 08:51.749
God wants to speak to you.

08:53.111 --> 08:55.133
If you're listening, he's going to speak.

08:55.193 --> 08:56.275
I can promise you that.

08:57.576 --> 09:00.079
So the Lord called Samuel a third time.

09:00.560 --> 09:02.482
And Samuel got up and went to Eli and said,

09:02.786 --> 09:03.888
Here I am, you called me.

09:03.928 --> 09:06.311
Then Eli realized that the Lord was calling the boy.

09:06.672 --> 09:08.835
So Eli told Samuel, go and lie down.

09:08.895 --> 09:12.721
And if he calls you, say, speak, Lord, for your servant is listening.

09:13.101 --> 09:16.106
So Samuel went and laid down in his place.

09:16.366 --> 09:19.691
And the Lord came and stood there, calling is at the other times.

09:20.112 --> 09:27.483
Samuel, Samuel, then Samuel said, speak for your servant is listening.

09:28.604 --> 09:29.746
So God is speaking.

09:30.786 --> 09:34.291
Now what I wanna do is I wanna give you just a few principles on God speaking.

09:34.331 --> 09:38.357
First of all, the very simple fact is God does speak.

09:38.377 --> 09:44.186
You have to settle that in your heart that there's a God who loves you so much that he wants relationship with you.

09:44.226 --> 09:48.532
And let me just add this, God speaks through his word.

09:48.612 --> 09:54.361
So you might have a verse jump off the page or you might hear a sermon and the word of God speaks to you.

09:54.661 --> 10:00.530
That is God speaking to you through his word, through a communicator of his word.

10:00.706 --> 10:01.668
God can speak.

10:02.028 --> 10:07.218
It may be a word from the Lord from through somebody to you.

10:07.238 --> 10:09.682
It's all kinds of ways God can speak.

10:11.285 --> 10:22.866
I know a lot of people want to say, well, you know the primary way God speaks is through his word, and I'm inclined to agree with that, but I'm afraid a lot of people hide behind that and consequently aren't really listening because they only

10:23.010 --> 10:30.738
have one way of seeing God speak to them, and I would suggest you could miss a lot of things a lot of prompting God would have for you.

10:33.041 --> 10:35.183
So God speaks.

10:35.203 --> 10:42.792
The boy Samuel ministered before the Lord under Eli, and in those days the word of the Lord was rare, and there were not many visions.

10:44.914 --> 10:52.402
One of the things that's true about when God is working, God is going,

10:52.482 --> 10:53.283
to speak.

10:54.906 --> 10:57.070
The question isn't, is God speaking?

10:57.571 --> 11:00.315
The question is, am I listening?

11:00.335 --> 11:09.851
In this situation, there's not much happening in the nation, and it really falls on Eli, but God is speaking, wants to speak anyway.

11:09.911 --> 11:12.155
So you may have never heard the voice of God.

11:12.215 --> 11:15.701
You may never have had God speak to you, but I can guarantee you this.

11:15.761 --> 11:18.546
God does want to speak to you because he's a God who speaks.

11:19.714 --> 11:23.598
Second, I want you to notice if God isn't speaking, something is wrong.

11:24.820 --> 11:32.528
Whenever God doesn't talk in the Old Testament, it's a sign of his displeasure in a situation.

11:33.349 --> 11:43.200
So in 1 Samuel, you have this story, Saul, the king at that time asked God, shall I go down after the Philistines, will you give them in the Israel's hand, but God did not answer him that day.

11:43.580 --> 11:48.786
So what happens is you have a king who isn't hearing from God because you have a king who is disobedient to God.

11:50.530 --> 12:01.727
The fact of the matter is, if our life isn't right with him, then it's gonna be hard for us, not only to hear from him, but he may not speak to us in the first place.

12:01.747 --> 12:07.816
This is why a pure heart makes all the difference in the world in hearing the voice of God.

12:08.777 --> 12:14.205
In 1 Samuel chapter 28, verse six, Saul inquired of the Lord, and the Lord did not answer him.

12:14.906 --> 12:17.650
Either by dreams, that's one way God speaks,

12:18.178 --> 12:20.962
Or by prophets, that's one way God speaks.

12:20.982 --> 12:24.606
Or by Urum, that was a way that the priest discerned the will of God.

12:24.927 --> 12:40.306
And honestly, it was a matter of taking many scholars believe it's either stones that had writing on them, so it might be yes, no, or it would be sticks that were thrown down and depending on, you know, and there was writing on them that was similar to yes or no.

12:41.026 --> 12:43.029
and the priest would discern the will of God.

12:43.049 --> 12:53.384
So here you have something that should be very simple, very mechanical, and not even it works, which tells you God's really silent at that moment.

12:54.185 --> 13:05.862
In the book of Amos, it says this, the days are coming to clear as the sovereign Lord, when I'll send a famine through the land, not a famine of food or a thirst for water, but a famine of hearing the words of the Lord.

13:05.922 --> 13:08.626
One of the signs of God's judgment is he goes silent.

13:10.690 --> 13:25.142
To that end, I would suggest if you're not with some regularity hearing the word of the Lord, and I'm talking especially to people who are more mature in their faith, if you're new to this, I don't want you to say, well, I'm not hearing it, so what's wrong?

13:26.204 --> 13:27.808
You're growing in your faith.

13:29.011 --> 13:30.514
But if you have

13:30.818 --> 13:33.262
More time in the Lord, more seasoning in the Lord.

13:33.623 --> 13:38.672
One of the things that should be true is the Lord should be speaking to your heart with regularity.

13:38.892 --> 13:40.896
It could be a prompting of your heart.

13:41.216 --> 13:42.599
It could be a reading of the word.

13:42.919 --> 13:44.642
It could be somebody giving you a word.

13:44.983 --> 13:47.187
It could be you praying and receiving from the Lord.

13:47.247 --> 13:51.755
But a part of walking with God is hearing his voice.

13:53.618 --> 13:55.922
And if you don't, you have to ask what's wrong.

13:57.602 --> 14:08.518
In verse Samuel three, there's a reason that Israel isn't hearing from God and it's related to their leader, they're being led by a priest by the name of Eli.

14:08.538 --> 14:16.570
The nation is led by him for 40 years, which was unusual to have a high priest doing that.

14:16.890 --> 14:21.056
But we learn about Eli in verse Samuel chapter three, verse one.

14:21.376 --> 14:23.219
In those days, the word of the Lord was rare.

14:23.560 --> 14:25.202
There were not many visions.

14:25.954 --> 14:30.481
One night Eli, whose eyes were becoming so weak that he could barely see.

14:30.881 --> 14:35.027
I want you to notice the connection between the physical and the spiritual.

14:37.631 --> 14:39.855
What I do physically affects me spiritually.

14:40.836 --> 14:42.639
What I do spiritually affects me physically.

14:43.921 --> 14:48.487
His physical condition is a metaphor for his spiritual condition.

14:48.888 --> 14:50.891
This is what the writer of Samuel is showing us.

14:51.271 --> 14:55.698
You got a priest that cannot see what God is doing and

14:56.226 --> 15:02.854
He's blind, not only physically, is he going blind, but he's going blind spiritually.

15:04.376 --> 15:05.317
Not many visions.

15:05.398 --> 15:06.239
His eyes are weak.

15:07.180 --> 15:10.404
His physical problem and illustration of his spiritual problem.

15:11.625 --> 15:14.309
It's no wonder visions are rare.

15:14.369 --> 15:17.172
The priest can't see.

15:17.212 --> 15:24.882
And if you're not hearing from God on a regular basis, then you got to say something is wrong.

15:26.946 --> 15:29.129
And I believe God shows us that.

15:29.469 --> 15:32.253
I believe God disturbs us over that.

15:32.533 --> 15:37.259
If you go through a season and yeah, you say, well, can't there be dry seasons in a person's life?

15:37.619 --> 15:40.463
And I'm not gonna discount that that cannot happen.

15:40.883 --> 15:51.136
I'm just saying the normative experience of the believer is that we walk and talk with God because God wants to walk and talk with us.

15:53.960 --> 15:55.922
And we hear his voice.

15:56.098 --> 15:58.702
And if you aren't, you have to say, Lord, what's wrong?

15:59.042 --> 16:00.104
I'm not hearing your voice.

16:02.126 --> 16:08.155
Is it something I've been doing intentionally that was displeasing to the Lord?

16:08.215 --> 16:09.857
Or was it something I didn't know?

16:09.897 --> 16:14.443
Maybe I didn't even think about it, but then you say, Lord, search me, show me.

16:14.804 --> 16:15.625
And he says, you know what?

16:16.506 --> 16:17.187
You did this.

16:19.771 --> 16:25.138
And you'll be surprised how when your heart is right with God, the voice of God,

16:25.250 --> 16:28.473
becomes much more prominent in your life.

16:29.955 --> 16:33.818
Number three, God speaks to those who are positioned to listen.

16:34.259 --> 16:36.841
I love this when you look at it in verse Samuel three.

16:36.861 --> 16:48.073
In those days the word of the Lord was rare and there were not many visions and one night Eli, whose eyes were becoming so weak he could barely see, was lying down in his usual place.

16:48.113 --> 16:53.618
The ESV says in his own place.

16:53.922 --> 16:58.107
It's not the temple at that time, although it uses the word temple in the NIV.

16:58.447 --> 17:04.855
It's the tabernacle, but there would be a place where the priest would stay near the tabernacle.

17:05.456 --> 17:09.421
But what you have here is you have Eli not staying in that place.

17:09.741 --> 17:11.003
He's staying in his own place.

17:12.885 --> 17:20.134
It's an intentional juxtaposition between what Eli is doing and what Samuel is doing.

17:20.174 --> 17:21.435
Look at it in verse three.

17:21.716 --> 17:23.698
The lamp of God had not yet gone out.

17:23.970 --> 17:29.738
And Samuel was lying down in the temple of the Lord where the ark of God was.

17:31.601 --> 17:33.584
So I didn't think anybody was allowed to go into the temple.

17:34.005 --> 17:36.308
Typically they wouldn't have been, but he's eight years old.

17:38.091 --> 17:40.574
And so he's just saying, you know what?

17:41.075 --> 17:43.579
The ark of the covenant is in the holy of holies.

17:43.959 --> 17:45.381
He's laying in the holy place.

17:45.642 --> 17:51.250
He's like, I'm gonna get as close to God's presence as I possibly can as an eight year old boy.

17:53.826 --> 17:56.489
He wants to be near God.

17:57.911 --> 18:03.859
Eli is lying down in his own place, which explains why he isn't hearing from God.

18:05.120 --> 18:10.507
Eli isn't in the presence of God in the same way that Samuel is.

18:12.550 --> 18:19.058
I mean, Eli's proximity to the presence of God is based on his personal preference.

18:19.714 --> 18:23.179
For him, it's not about being as close to God as possible.

18:23.760 --> 18:32.532
It's about being as close to God as is convenient.

18:32.552 --> 18:39.442
I think this is a very thought-provoking passage in this sense.

18:40.784 --> 18:47.634
What is your commitment to being not only in the presence of God

18:47.842 --> 18:50.225
but being as close as you can to the presence of God.

18:51.846 --> 19:00.276
Because sometimes we can have the idea that because I'm in the presence of God, that's the same as being close to the presence of God, and that's not necessarily so.

19:02.778 --> 19:09.666
You can have proximity to the presence without really being close to His presence.

19:11.688 --> 19:14.051
And here's the startling reality in all of this.

19:15.072 --> 19:17.234
Samuel is what Eli used to be.

19:20.098 --> 19:21.760
There was a day when Eli was close.

19:23.523 --> 19:25.125
There was a day when Eli did care.

19:28.490 --> 19:48.498
Which again is a startling reality for us that we could start loving God, seeking God, desiring God, but through time, neglect, and our own personal preferences and pursuits, find ourselves in a place where when we look at our life, we're living in a time

19:48.610 --> 19:51.273
when closeness to God was in another time.

19:53.635 --> 19:57.099
My question to you is, are you as close to God as you've ever been?

19:57.139 --> 20:00.863
And if you're not, why not?

20:02.205 --> 20:15.219
And if you're not, do you understand that that distance that has come between you and God is problematic and will keep you from experiencing God's best in your life and it will keep you from hearing God's voice in your life?

20:17.121 --> 20:18.322
Here's what's interesting.

20:18.850 --> 20:22.235
The Lord is calling out Samuel, Samuel.

20:24.339 --> 20:28.666
And Samuel can hear it, but he like him.

20:28.686 --> 20:34.736
He's close enough that Samuel can run to him, but he cannot hear the voice of God.

20:36.358 --> 20:37.901
Here's a lesson for all of us.

20:38.201 --> 20:46.194
If you're walk with God becomes more about personal preference than a passionate pursuit of God's presence, you will lose your ability to hear God's voice.

20:48.290 --> 21:08.056
This is where all of us have to, like we talked about last week, stay hungry so that hearing the voice of God, passionately being close to God, saying, God, I want as much of you as I can have, and I certainly want more than I had yesterday.

21:08.116 --> 21:12.562
You say, well, I mean,

21:12.706 --> 21:14.088
Is that really ours to claim?

21:14.348 --> 21:17.273
Oh yeah, we go from glory to glory to glory to glory.

21:17.653 --> 21:24.443
God's desire is for you and I to get closer and closer and closer, not hit a point and then stay there.

21:24.503 --> 21:27.067
He wants us to know him more.

21:27.487 --> 21:32.775
Even Moses who speaks to him face to face as a man speaks to his friend, says, God, I want to see your glory.

21:32.795 --> 21:34.738
And God says, great, I'll show it to you.

21:36.034 --> 21:45.987
He has a passion for the presence of God and for closeness to God and God honors that by revealing something to him nor the human being has experienced.

21:47.509 --> 21:50.092
So it's important to desire it.

21:51.434 --> 21:58.743
In verse three it says this, the lamp of God had not yet gone out and Samuel was lying down in the temple of the Lord.

21:59.043 --> 22:02.368
He's getting as close to God as he possibly can.

22:02.388 --> 22:04.210
I mean,

22:04.290 --> 22:09.517
So if the Lord comes out from the holy of holies, he's gonna have to step over Samuel.

22:12.260 --> 22:13.642
That's Samuel's intent.

22:13.702 --> 22:18.429
God, if you're gonna move, I'm gonna be so close to you, you're gonna have to step on me.

22:19.871 --> 22:23.435
I wanna be so close to you that I wanna hear your voice.

22:23.455 --> 22:30.905
So we're not surprised when we read this that the Lord called Samuel.

22:30.925 --> 22:31.666
Number four.

22:31.810 --> 22:33.813
God speaks to those who want to hear him.

22:33.833 --> 22:35.255
This is really the good news.

22:36.277 --> 22:42.907
A desire to hear God is really the basis for hearing God.

22:45.151 --> 22:45.952
You want to hear God?

22:46.312 --> 22:47.714
I believe God wants you to hear him.

22:48.676 --> 22:50.278
That's good, isn't it?

22:50.298 --> 22:54.705
The Lord desires to show himself to us.

22:57.490 --> 23:00.434
He desires to show us things we do not know.

23:02.914 --> 23:04.116
It's what he has for us.

23:05.338 --> 23:15.052
The Lord came and stood there calling as at the other time, Samuel, Samuel, then Samuel said, speak for your servant is listening.

23:15.473 --> 23:23.304
Really, this is the prayer every single one of us should in our heart be praying, Lord, speak.

23:24.706 --> 23:25.347
I'm listening.

23:27.190 --> 23:29.614
The Bible talks about inclining our ear to the Lord.

23:29.634 --> 23:32.498
Sometimes we have to lean in to hear closely.

23:33.346 --> 23:34.267
or do you hear clearly?

23:35.569 --> 23:41.796
Sometimes that means, you know, sometimes God is whispering and the only way you're gonna hear it is if you get really close to Him.

23:42.737 --> 23:53.731
And part of the reason why God whispers is because He wants you to know what that closeness feels like because He not only wants you close to Him, He wants to be close to you.

23:54.351 --> 23:56.734
This is the God who loves us more than we could imagine.

23:58.176 --> 24:03.282
And when you're close to God and when you desire the things of God, what happens is God begins

24:03.458 --> 24:05.660
to tell you things you would not know.

24:08.002 --> 24:12.307
I love the way Psalm 25 puts it in the message.

24:12.707 --> 24:14.609
God friendship is for God worshipers.

24:14.989 --> 24:16.491
They're the ones He confides in.

24:16.991 --> 24:26.780
When you are walking close to God, God is gonna tell you things you would never know on your own.

24:26.800 --> 24:32.626
He's gonna speak to you for your own good and for the good of people around you.

24:35.362 --> 24:39.608
I just, I desire that for myself, I desire it for you.

24:40.850 --> 25:02.642
And I'm thrilled because when I look at the church, I say I've never seen a time in the, in the life of the church where I've seen people more readily wanting to hear God's voice and God more obviously speaking to them things to their heart, things that are touching other people's lives, things that are building people up.

25:04.610 --> 25:07.058
And so God wants to speak to you.

